{"name": "django-phonenumbers", "metadata": {"name": "django-phonenumbers", "version": "1.0.1", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Environment :: Web Environment", "Framework :: Django :: 1.7", "Framework :: Django :: 1.8", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only"], "home_page": "https://github.com/iraklikhitarishvili/django_phonenumbers", "license": "BSD License", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Phone number field for Django admin", "upload_time": 1438857917}, "documentation": ["# Installation\n\n```\nrun  pip install django_phonenumbers\n```\n\n# Configure settings.py\n\n```\nAdd django_phonenumbers to INSTALLED_APPS\n```\n\n# manage.py\n\n```\nrun manage.py collectstatic\n```\n\n# settings.py\n\n```python\nPHONE_NUMBER_REGION = 'GE'\nPHONE_NUMBERS_FORMATS_BY_REGION = {\n    'GE': {\n        'pattern': '(\\\\d{3})(\\\\d{2})(\\\\d{2})(\\\\d{2})', 'format': '\\\\1 \\\\2-\\\\3-\\\\4', 'prefix_format': '+%s (%s)'\n    },\n    'US': {\n        'pattern': '(\\\\d{3})(\\\\d{3})(\\\\d{4})', 'format': '\\\\1 \\\\2-\\\\3', 'prefix_format': '+%s (%s)'\n    },\n}\n```\n\n- \"PHONE_NUMBER_REGION\" determines which country region will be selected in admin's corresponding phone number field\n- \"PHONE_NUMBERS_FORMATS_BY_REGION\" is used in \"phone_number_format\" filter\n\n# Model\n\n```python\n#models.py\nclass MyModel(models.Model):\n    ...\n    phone_number = PhoneNumberField()\n    ...\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return str(self.phone_number)\n```\n\n**\"phone_number\"** field's type will be **\"PhoneNumber\"**\n\n```python\nclass PhoneNumber:\n    def __init__(self, country_code=None, region_code=None, phone_number=None):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type country_code: str\n        :type region_code: str\n        :type phone_number: str\n        \"\"\"\n        self.country_code = country_code\n        self.google_phone_number = None\n        self.region_code = region_code\n        self.phone_number = phone_number\n```\n\n\"\\_\\_str\\_\\_\" and \"\\_\\_repr\\_\\_\" functions are overridden to return \"country_code\"+\" \"+\"phone_number\"\n\n**model.fields.PhoneNumberField** is using **form.fields.PhoneNumberField** in admin by default\n\n**model.fields.PhoneNumberField** and **form.fields.PhoneNumberField** is validating and formatting(in national format) entered number\n\n# Template example\n\n```html\n<li>\n            {{ number.phone_number }}\n            // {{ number.phone_number.region_code }}\n            // {{ number.phone_number.country_code }}\n            // {{ number.phone_number.phone_number }}\n            <div>\n                {% load phone_numbers_extra %}\n                <h4>Filter\n                    <small>{{ number.phone_number|phone_number_format }}</small>\n                </h4>\n                <h4>Simple tag\n                    <small>\n                        {% phone_number number.phone_number pattern='(\\\\d{3})(\\\\d{3})(\\\\d{3})' number_format='\\\\1 \\\\2-\\\\3' prefix_format='+%s (%s)' %}\n                    </small>\n                </h4>\n            </div>\n</li>\n```\n\n**phone_number_format** uses **PHONE_NUMBERS_FORMATS_BY_REGION** from settings.py to determine phone number format\n\n# Example\n\n```\n'GE': {  'pattern': '(\\\\d{3})(\\\\d{2})(\\\\d{2})(\\\\d{2})', 'format': '\\\\1 \\\\2-\\\\3-\\\\4', 'prefix_format': '+%s (%s)'},\n```\n\n- 'GE' : region code\n- 'pattern'\n  : - 3 digits\n    - 2 digits\n    - 2 digits\n    - 2 digits\n- 'format' : `'\\\\1 \\\\2-\\\\3-\\\\4'` numbers are groups mentioned above. for example if you want to put last 2 digits in scopes you should write '\\\\1 \\\\2-\\\\3-(\\\\4)' and result will be xxx xx-xx-(xx)\n- 'prefix_format' : '+%s (%s)' first \"%s\" is country code second mobile operator or city code for example +995 (595) where 995 is my country code and 595 my mobile operator's code you can change formatting fore example '[%s] [%s]' will give [995] [595] this result\n\nwith this simple tag you can specify format inline\n\n```python\n{% phone_number number.phone_number pattern='(\\\\d{3})(\\\\d{3})(\\\\d{3})' number_format='\\\\1 \\\\2-\\\\3' prefix_format='+%s (%s)' %}\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "django_phonenumbers.templatetags.phone_numbers_extra", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "django_phonenumbers.templatetags.phone_numbers_extra.phone_number_format", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "number", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "region_code", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_phonenumbers.templatetags.phone_numbers_extra.phone_number", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "number", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "region_code", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "pattern", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "number_format", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "prefix_format", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["for number +995595119925\npattern=\"(\\d{3})(\\d{2})(\\d{2})(\\d{2})\", format=\"\\1 \\2-\\3-\\4\"\nresult 595 11-99-25"]}], "variables": [{"name": "django_phonenumbers.templatetags.phone_numbers_extra.register", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "django_phonenumbers.templatetags", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "django_phonenumbers.templatetags.__author__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "django_phonenumbers", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "django_phonenumbers.tests", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "django_phonenumbers.model", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "django_phonenumbers.model.__author__", "type": null